# A guide on how to BYOD (Bring Your Own Domain) to Astroid

The guide below assumes youâ€™re attempting to **link a FreeDNS subdomain** to Astroid.
1. Open https://freedns.afraid.org and https://smailpro.com
2. On Smailpro, click the Green "Open" button.
3. Click the + icon on top of "@example.com" to generate a temporary email. Click on the generated email to copy it.
4. Go back to FreeDNS, and click "Sign Up Free".
5. Fill out the required information. First and last name doesn't have to be real but make sure to enter a User ID and password you will remember. Agree to the terms and conditions and send the account activation email.
6. Return to Smailpro and click the refresh button in the blue box that says "Inbox".
7. Open the email, copy the activation URL, and paste it into a new tab.
8. Click "Registry".
9 Find a domain you want, and click it.
10. Make sure next to type, `A` is selected. For subdomain, enter anything you want. This will be what's before the domain (subdomain.domain.com) The destination should be **`5.161.68.227`**.
11. Complete the captcha and save your changes.
12. Wait a few minutes, then go to the subdomain you created.
